1. If everyone in society acted ethically, then the system of man that would be irrelevant would be the justice system, or law. This
is because there's no need to enforce any rules if everyone is essentially working together in harmony towards the greater good.

2. A great example in recent history that benefited the group at the detriment to the individual was the Industrial Revolution in America.
This is because the economy and general standard of living skyrocketed in America but to the normal factory worker, they didn't really feel
the benefits until much later in life. 

